oc:kn_1614a6a7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a CRO experiment program" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prioritize experiments by page type: homepage (hero, trust), pricing (presentation, UX), demo/form pages (field optimization), landing pages (message match), feature pages (demo/proof). Each page type has distinct high-impact test categories." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Page-specific testing yields faster wins because each page serves a different conversion purpose and audience intent." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7d15f294 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building an experimentation roadmap for any page" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For each page type, test in this order: (1) above-fold messaging and CTAs, (2) trust/social proof elements, (3) content structure and ordering, (4) navigation and friction reduction. Higher-impact areas first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Above-fold changes reach all visitors and typically show the largest conversion lift; trust elements address hesitation; structure tests optimize the mid-page; navigation tests are incremental." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d9a54881 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning multiple experiments at once" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not run more than one test on the same page element simultaneously — tests must be isolated to attribute results accurately. Cross-page site-wide tests (chat widget, cookie consent, page speed) should be run separately from page-specific tests." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overlapping tests on the same page create interaction effects that make results unreliable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e2f8184b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting which experiments to prioritize from this catalog" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid testing only superficial elements (button colors, minor copy tweaks) while ignoring structural and messaging experiments (headline strategy, page length, navigation removal, form field count). Structural changes typically yield larger conversion lifts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Minor visual changes rarely move conversion rates meaningfully; hypothesis-driven structural changes have higher ROI." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_fd621285 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recommending any A/B test from this catalog" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every experiment must pair a specific test change with a clear hypothesis. The tables provide the test variation and the hypothesized outcome — always frame recommendations as 'If we change X, then Y will happen because Z.'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without a hypothesis, test results are uninterpretable and cannot generate cumulative learning." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

